Share this on WhatsAppThe All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) has nominated Professor Chukwuma Soludo, former Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), as the party’s candidate for the November 6, 2021 governorship election in Anambra State.
It was gathered the Soludo won the APGA governorship ticket with 740 votes of the 790 total votes cast at the party’s state primary election in Anambra State to defeat three other aspirants.
Meanwhile, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has released a list of delegates to the primary election to nominate its governorship candidate.
